,Recommended,310080,12080528,"Posted: 12 September, 2014",all,twitch.tv/tofutehsurvivor,"Where do I stat with this? It's difficult to classify this game as something other than a dating sim, because it can become more than that depending on your choices. It's also very difficult to discuss this game without resorting to ""omg look at this wacky game! It's soooooooo random! XD"" Don't let the Pewdiepie hype portrayed by many streamers deter you from even glancing at this due to your disgust. Those people are the same idiots that also scream, ""Dark Souls is too hard! Golly, this is so epic!""I can say, first and foremost, that this is a visual novel. Regardless of sub-genre, that's what this boils down to.It's a very intriguing visual novel. It performs under the guise of a classic Japanese high school dating sim while donning the peculiar gimmick of having birds for the school's students. While this may sound extremely gimmicky, and I won't lie, it is. That is not necessarily a bad thing though! This allows for a different kind of exploration into one's feelings.Can you get emotionally attatched to a bird to some degree?You would not think so, but these birds are essentially people-type characters. They talk, have inner/outter conflicts, and even run in marathons. I can also imagine the same could happen if it was a high school ofSuper Robots, but it's not. That would be an awesome game. We need that to be on Steam right now.If you're still interested at this point you'd might as well start reading further into this. Let's face it; if you're interested in a dating sim with birds, then you probably have few other things to entertain you at this point in terms of modern gaming.Would I even like a dating sim with birds where I would not be able to even date females?That's how I felt, but I was tired of the typical tropes of AAA games and decided that I would instead let myself fall victim to the cliches of standardized Japanese gaming this time around. I was absolutely correct in the aspect of dating sim cliches remaining intact, but I was not prepared for the fact that there are routes that rip the afforementioned apart. If you're reading through Fate/Stay Night, then of course you'd expect things to become intense and heavy. When you play an average dating sim you're just expecting two people to get together and happy things ensue with a nice ending, save for School Days. That was just depressing on about every level.You won't expect things once they hit you in Hatoful Boyfriend, and that is the true glory of the writing in this game. It just happens to be covered in a feathery layer topped with a beak.I fully recommend this title to visual novel enthusiasts, or anyone who just wants to dive into the visual novel genre for their first time. With a title like this being easily accessible to a North American audience on Steam, there has never been a better time to start!"
