,Recommended,310080,12907880,"Posted: 11 November, 2014",all,PortableOpossum,"On the surface, this game seems completely stupid; something that you would buy only as a joke. After binge playing this game with all my free time for about 4 days, I can honestly say that this may be in my top 3 games for this year. This game actually has a serious story. One that you need to get all of the endings to put together and one that will make you step away from the keyboard after you're done and say ""What the hell just happened?"" This game is amazing. I never once thought I would be attached to any of these characters but there were times when I legitimately almost teared up. This game is funny. It's sad. It's downright tragic. You are doing yourself a disservice by not picking up this game. And you are doing yourself a bigger disservice if you already have it, got one ending, and dismissed it. As someone who has played quite few visual novel type games I can say without a shred of hesitation this is one of the best. 10/10, would attend St. PigeoNation's again."
