76561198031149034,Recommended,310080,12214615,"Posted: 23 September, 2014",all,blumouse42,"As someone who normally doesn't like dating sims, I only played this game because it looked funny and a bit unique. ""A dating sim, but all the boys are pigeons?"" I thought, ""Sounds incredible, I have to play."" And sure enough, it was incredible. Just not in the way I expected.Hatoful Boyfriend is funny, it's true, it has a very funny and quirky sense of humor that will be incredibly enjoyable for anyone who enjoys puns or jokes that almost slip under your radar, but when you catch them make you snort with amusment. Oh, and the fact that your character, as the only human in a school full of pigeons, is treated in the same stereotypical way that a singular intellegent bird would probably be treated if the situation was reversed (""stereotypical"" human/primate behavior, constant references to her species in both jokes and regular conversation, she literally lives in a cave), is very funny as well. However, the real charm of Hatoful Boyfriend is when it is not being funny. This game, at times, is much more serious than you would think possible, even heartwrenching and disturbing. This game will make you laugh, it will make you cry, and it will constantly shock you (assuming you manage to avoid spoilers before playing, which is very recommended as the shock is part of the game's charm) and keep you interested and wanting to play all the way to the end.I pirated this game years ago expecting a joke game and now I've bought the $15 special edition on steam because I believe that this game absolutely deserves every penny. This game has made such a big impact on me, it is easily one of the best visual novel-type games that I have ever played and I would absolutely reccommend it to anyone and everyone with the attention span for visual novels. Even if you don't think you have the attention span, watch a playthrough or try it out somehow because this is one game that really should not be missed. Also I just want to mention that the music is incredible.tl;drCome for the pigeons, stay for the amazing story and shocking turns (and the great bgm)."
