,Recommended,310080,14967178,"Posted: 19 March, 2015",all,Orangerrific,"With every single bit of seriousness my body can muster, out of every game I've played, this is genuinely one of the best written stories I have ever had the pleasure of playing through, PERIOD. Most people will look at this game, play through maybe one or two routes, write it off as ""jokey birb game"", and, unfortunately, never touch it again. Which sucks, considering the real meat of this game lies in the epilogue, where the genre does a complete 180.This game goes from animu-like dating sim with some hilarious parodies of a lot of visual novel tropes (with the exception of the Nageki route, which deals with some very heavy subjects), to a murder mystery full of twists and turns, with some surprisingly disturbing horror elements thrown in. There were at least three different points where I thought the game was about to end, but it just kept throwing more and more curveballs at me.The core game is full of wonderful silliness and knows what it is. The characters and their personalities are memorable and hilarious.Definitely a must-complete kind of game. Took me around 10 hours to go through every route and get the true ending. :)"
