,Recommended,310080,33774119,Posted: 24 July,all,フィンチ,"I don't think i'm able to properly describe it without spoiling it. I was opening it thinking i'd spend a night playing a fun parody visual novel. Some people mentioned it made them cry in the end, and i thought maybe there's gonna be some exaggerated parody pigeon drama. I was not ready to see what laid beneath it, oh no, not at all.BBL route was possibly the most powerful series of plot twists that i've ever read. And what makes it so great is how with every one of them, you realise that it's not just random edgy stuff added to shock the player, but actually everything you have seen throughout the game is connected and tied very well. The contrast of the actual story with what you originally think it is is just adding to the experience.It wasn't anywhere close to what i expected, but i didn't regret it at all (maybe just a bit, when i finished playing at 2 AM and couldn't make myself go to bed after that, because it turned out to be too overwhelming for me).I'd really like more people to play it. This is art."
