76561198024760864,Not Recommended,310080,32754365,Posted: 24 June,all,ant,"I've done three characters' routes so far, so perhaps it isn't accurate to judge the game with only this short amount of time, but I felt the need to explain some issues I have with it now, because of the lack serious critical reviews that accentuate some of the flaws of the game.*I understand this is somewhat of a ""joke game"" but I want there to be an honest review out there for anyone expecting more*- There is no option to scroll back to text you just read through- Saves frequently glitch out so that text is never displayed when you load them, rendering them useless.- Sometimes steam will not register that you completed a route, and won't give the proper achievement.- The skip button does not stop at unread text, which would be more of a problem if any new text got added until the last few lines of each route. Events barely change based on your choices, if at all.- While the characters are interesting, they are given no time to be fleshed out in their routes because scenes start and end so quickly. You get maybe ten lines of text, often times less, in scenes like the festival or sports event. The difference between a good endign and a bad ending for the routes that have multiple ones is a small bit of extra text at the very end.- A lot of the jokes fall flat, referencing anime tropes, etc. which was probably intentional given that the game is meant for the shock value. I can give this a pass because it is trying to recreate a stereotypical date sim.- The stat-raising element is pointless and makes an otherwise mind-numbingly simple game frustrating to solve without a walkthrough. Example: for some reason, not hinted at anywhere, you can only getShuu's good endingif youpick ""math"" for your elective every time.- Some of the character portraits are blurry on larger resolutions. The audio is pretty good aside from some low quality sound effects and at least one music track I recognize as most likely stock music.I really like the over-the-top personalities and I think they really could've hit it out of the park if they were given more time to develop. Once you've gone through the game one time you can skip through every bit of in-between dialogue that isn't character specific, leaving around 20 minutes of actual gameplay per route.It's times like these where I wish you could select an option between ""no"" and ""yes"" in steam reviews because, for what the game is, it's very cute. When it's shocking, it's shocking. when it's funny, it's funny. Perhaps the game improves in the final route (I already feel things bubbling under the surface) but the lack of comforts of a typical visual novel and general lack of functionality make it REALLY uncomfortable to drudge through the game several times over, despite how short it really is."
