76561198118473843,Recommended,310080,17729274,"Posted: 26 August, 2015",all,weeblecat,"Last night I stayed up two hours past bedtime on a work night because I was so engrossed in the life-or-death adventures of sexy high school pigeons. Thank you for giving me the opportunity to write that sentence, Hatoful Boyfriend.You either like the idea of ""visual novel where girl dates sapient anime-trope pigeons"" or you don't, so it should be easy to decide if this game is for you. But here's the thing: if you like the idea, you're going to like the game more than that. While all the characters are recognizable tropes, they're executed in engaging ways. The main character herself is weird and enthusiastic and charming. The writing (and translation) is light and humorous until the moments where suddenly it's *not*, and the transitions there are nimble. came for the lols, stayed for the surprising quality.And then there's the BBL route, the one you unlock after you've gotten an ending with each major character. Do yourself a favor and clear all the other endings first, both so you'll have as much character background as possible and so you can unlock the epilogue right away. Then clear a few hours to play through the whole thing -- it probably took almost half my total play time -- make the ""fulfill a promise from long ago"" choice at the start of a new game, and let your hunter-gatherer instincts lead the way.Pigeon dating sim: why so great."
