76561198093535643,Recommended,310080,15865603,"Posted: 16 May, 2015",all,WastelandCola (Bryan),"Now let me start off by saying ""this is not just a silly dating sim"". Well I guess it is but their's so much more to it than just dating birds.Story: Surprisingly the game has a well crafted story with great writing and multiple endings depending on which bird you romance. All the characters feel unique with there own personalities, interests, and quirks. The story itself will branch out into different paths, that are amazing and heartfelt. It also helps that Hatoful Boyfriend is very replayable.Gameplay: Just like any visual novel, the gameplay boils down to reading text boxes and occasionally making a decision. Which isn't a bad thing as long as your prepared for it and know what you're getting into.Presentation: The game has a very cute art style that goes for more cartoonish than realistic and the fact that the character models are cut out from actual pictures of birds is a nice touch. Unfortunately a lot of areas get reused do to the setting of the game.Verdict: Hatoful Boyfriend is a charming game with some slight problems that fortunately aren't that bad or game breaking. So in conclusion Hatoful Boyfriend gets a 9/10. It is a must buy. It has great quality for a ten dollar game."
