,Recommended,310080,24100492,"Posted: 4 July, 2016",all,NTTGSLOT,"An absolutely wonderful buy! An April Fool's day joke gone way too far in the best way possible.""Quirky"" is an excellent way to describe this game. At first glance, it's easily overlooked and labelled as 'too weird' and 'odd', but rest assured the game itself is much more fantastic than that. (Although, to be fair, the oddity is a part of its charm.) Go in with an open mind and it isn't hard to be sucked into this world and all its shenanigans.The re-release has updated the graphics beautifully and any fan of otome games with a good sense of humor is bound to love this game. The save option in the bottom right-hand corner makes it incredibly easy pause the game whenever necessary and pick up exactly where you left off without having to wait for a check-point or anything of the sort.The routes and birds are all very entertaining and lovable in their own ways. Nageki is my personal favorite and I fell in LOVE as soon as I saw him (possibly loved him even more after I found out about his tragic backstory). They'll make you cry, laugh, scream, coo, and give you a reason to see each one of their endings. Luckily, it's not hard to achieve these endings either seeing as a mistake or two will still typically allow you to complete the route (with the exception of a few birds if you choose to get their ""Best end"" or ""full end"" routes).Another note worth mentioning is that the protagonist of this game is very well done! For most otome games, I personally find the protagonists to lack a little bit of personality and tend to be quite generic (this is usually due to the fact that the player's choices determine what the protagonist's personality is like) but with this game, there is no worry. Hiyoko (if you choose to maintain the default name) is as amusing as she is quirky, and her cheerful hunter-gatherer demeanor will work its way into your heart just as well as any of the other birds in the game while maintaining the ability to make personalized choices.If you enjoyed Hatoful Boyfriend and have not bought the DLC, then I suggest you go do so. The same goes for the holiday sequel, Hatoful Boyfriend: Holiday Star (which has extra content) and is a must-buy if you fell in love with the characters and their stories like I did.10/10 Would buy again. Would play again. Coo Coo!!!(BBL lay waste to my heart...)"
