,Recommended,310080,19901852,"Posted: 24 December, 2015",all,Groxworld1,"I can't believe the day has come when I can unironically recommend a video game about dating pigeons, but to be fair I did also unironically recommend Euro Truck Simulator 2.Hatoful Boyfriend (if you're wondering, ""hatoful"" could be read as ""heartful"" or ""hurtful""; and also triples as a pun to the Japanese kanji for pigeon) shows that no matter how silly the premise, you can still make a great story out of it. What originally started out as a visual novel about dating pigeons, eventually becomes a visual novel about dating pigeons with deep and complex personalities.The game (or should I say the visual novel) itself is nothing complex, the closest thing to gameplay here is making a decision. Though your decision will ultimately decide who you choose to get close with and how the game ends.Speaking of the story, it is quite entertaining. The writing is fantastic, and all of the characters have their own lovable quirks, in fact the route you take can vastly affect the mood of the story. After going on a certain route, you can do the hidden route which unless you've gotten all the ending (which includes both the normal and true ending for every character) you won't see the epilogue. Getting all of the ending means you have to read through a lot of the things you've read before, there is a fast forward button; but sometimes new dialogues could appear in a scene that you expected to play as usual.Overall Hatoful Boyfriend is an entertaining visual novel about dating pigeons...That was anti-climatic."
