,Recommended,310080,15798344,"Posted: 12 May, 2015",all,❀ 티타니아 ❀,"When I first got the game, I found it rather shallow and boring.After months of putting it off, I finally decided to hunt down all the achievements and storyline I was missing.I made the right choice.Hatoful Boyfriend has a deeper and rich storyline that I never expected to have when I first bought it. On first look, it's just a regular dating simulation. How wrong I was. As you gradually take time to understand each character, you start learning about the secrets that were harboured in the school itself. Ultimately, you confront yourself with a sinister plot that would not have been expected at first.Characters and storyline are well developed enough to leave an impression on you. The music works well in relation to the story and happenings at the point they're played, although sound effects in certain parts of the game seems a little overdone. They still work, since it fits the storyline and has to be in place for the experience of players.Frankly speaking, I am still amazed by the tension and humour the joke of a bird dating simulation has given me. I'm glad I decided to pick up Hatoful Boyfriend and I enjoyed it very much."
