,Recommended,310080,15332284,"Posted: 12 April, 2015",all,Arcanelevitator,"Hatoful Boyfriend is a game originally released in 2011 in Japan and has been rereleased globally in 2014 onto Steam.We have seen various dating simulators on Steam which have been pretty mediocre (not that I have played any of them...). However this game should be the No. 1 priority for Steam users if they are looking into immersing themselves in visual novels for the first time. Of course, users can play visual novels that are not on Steam such as Katawa Shoujo (which is exceptionally good by the way), but we should seize the opportunity Lord GabeN has given us, allowing us to play dating simulators on the legendary platform known as Steam. So don't lose this opportunity!Hatoful Boyfriend is a visual novel game in which the player dates pigeons. Although this may sound like an unusual concept, we gamers are always looking out on the market for the latest innovative games which bring new concepts and ideas to the congested video game market. Although the visual novel genre isn't especially innovative, the idea of having a romantic relationship between the protagonist, you, and various male pigeons is certainly innovative. Therefore I am giving this game a thumbs up.This may seem like a review just to laud the game's innovation and creativity. However, the gameplay and graphics are also up to par with the other releases which have come out at around the same time as this game. Even though this game is a visual novel, it provides immersive gameplay which will keep players like myself hooked on for hours at a time. The soundtrack for the game is one of the best in the market, which is why I purchased the Digital Deluxe version of the game, which includes the song's soundtrack!PositivesExceptional graphics (Can be considered a benchmarking tool similar to what Ryse: Son of Rome was on PC).Exceptional storyline (Not as good as Barbie Dreamhouse Party but still better than The Last of Us).Exceptional optimization (Runs better than Assassin's Creed: Unity).Exceptional gameplay (Combine Flappy Bird and Angry Birds).Exceptional characters (Especially Okosan).MixedNo nudity (Depends whether you like nude pigeons or not. If you do, I do not know if there is an uncensored version out there...).NegativeNo anti-aliasing (I feel like the graphics could be even more amazing if there was some anti-aliasing).Not enough pigeons (I need more to suppress my desires...).Even though this game has some negatives about it, I would still consider it to be GOTY. We all know there is no such thing as a perfect video game. The positives heavily outweigh the negatives and that is all that matters. So therefore, I hope that you have carefully read this review and will pick this game up as soon as possible. If you are not overly convinced that this game is amazing yet, I suggest reading the other 1,500 or so reviews on the store page!8/8(I hope you didn't expect this review to be legitimate XD)"
