76561198082496093,Recommended,310080,12962592,"Posted: 15 November, 2014",all,FritzingHell,"9/10 - A MUST OWN FOR ANYONE WHO LOVES FANTASTIC STORIES IN THEIR GAMESHoo boy, I have gotten a LOT of flack from my friends when playing this game.  And to some degree, I agree with them.  A great deal of this was only mildly entertaining and I did not understand why people (especially close friends of mine) loved this game.  The game begins with the main character (a female...  yes, you play a female in a dating sim...) starting her sophomore year [unsure if right or not] and during the next year dates several bird-boy-people-things...  NOW, you must be wondering, ""Why is a girl dating birds!?  How can she develop intimate feelings for these avian creatures!?  HOW CAN THE BIRDS FRICKIN' ACT LIKE HUMAN BEINGS!?!?!?""  Put those questions aside when you play the story, but just don't forget about them entirely.Each character's dating route got progressively more funny and interesting the more I played it, EXCEPT FOR ONE which made me feel like I was mashing my head against a wall for doing something so inanely stupid as it was not a good route to take...  If you play the game, you will know the one because you will think the main character is dumb.  After playing through just about every route at least once, I unlocked a new route that was only available to begin in the beginning.  THIS FINAL ROUTE, HOO BOY IT WAS A DOOZY!This final route made the entire game so much more worth it, and answered soooooooo maaaaaannyyyyyy quuueeestions!  OH, and if you want to do the epilogue, you need to get all endings before doing the Final Route (There are some characters with TWO endings, one being a normal ending and the other being a TRUE ending...).I am not really going to talk about the final route too much, but let me just say that this game was a rollercoaster of funny moments and intense plots.I TOTALLY RECOMMEND THIS GAME, but it sometimes felt annoying to play through a route again JUST for the epilogue...  Good thing this game has a skip function to speed through text...  Saved me MUCH MORE TIME than I would have done, if that function wasn't in the game.In short, if you love games with fantastic stories, GET THIS GAME NOW!"
