,Recommended,310080,28157801,"Posted: 3 December, 2016",all,recta1anarchy,"There's no doubt this game is rough around the edges, but under the surface lies strange, wonderful things. I'm trying to keep spoilers to a minimum for this, but there's gonna be some.This game is about dating fictional birds. Fictional. Birds. The setting may be ridiculous and silly, and the gameisridiculous and silly, but it has a surprising amount of depth. Being a new student at St. Pidgeonation's high school, you have the option of dating a total of 9 birds. The first few routes (Ryouta, Sakuya, Nageki, etc.) are fairly easy to complete and find, but there are a few well hidden ones that grant a deeper (or more silly) look at the world that Mediatronic and co. built.Speaking of the world, it has very little consistency. While the majority of it is explained away inYuuya's routeandBBL routethe story just doesn't hold for a lot of what we see. That is kind of expected - it isn't easy or even necessary to build a wholly consistent world for what is a mostly comedic game. But, strangely, there is a surprising amount of lore that is explained throughout the game, especially in the de-facto true ending.That lore involves a rollercoaster of emotions. What is essentially a comedic game devolves into a tragedy by the end, if you're willing to stick through it. Mind you, good luck keeping that will. Some parts do drag on for too long (which is very annoying in a visual novel) and the bright and happy UI impairs the immersion when the situation is dire. If you like your story with twists, though, this game will not dissapoint. Just be prepared to sit through a few hours of glorious bird dating first. On the other hand, if you only want to date those birds, don't pick to complete the promise when you get the chance. It's a major change in tone and there's really no bird dating involved in that route.Gameplay-wise, it's a visual novel with RPG elements. While the RPG elements are only useful in a couple of routes, they are important to getting some of the good endings for some characters as well as finishing them altogether. I suggest using a guide because things can get messy very quickly and you WILL miss some routes without one. The visual novel aspect, on the other hand... it's a ren'py game, and it is hard to say much beyond that. There are some minor bugs here and there, but they aren't game breaking.It's a solid visual novel / dating sim with a surprising amount of depth and plot on the inside. As a bird dating sim, it's a 7/10. With all the twists and world involved, I'm willing to give it an 8 for the effort, even if it isn't executed perfectly.8/10."
