,Recommended,310080,33112109,Posted: 1 July,all,Zeta_Riemann,"This is probably one of my favourite games of all time.. Wait no scratch that. It's definitely one of my favourite games of all time. Hatoful Boyfriend is the epic tale of a hunter-gatherer girl who must go on the adventure of a life time.At first glance, most people have assumed this game is just a silly game about dating pigeons, but if you've actually finished the whole thing you know it's so much more than that. Not only is it filled with a rich history, wonderfully refreshing characters, and a compelling original story, but it knows how to have fun.  I've played quite a few visual novels and dating sims, and I can say that even after you've only played two or three, they can get repetitive fast. No matter how much you like them, it's easy to notice how similar they all are with most characters only existing to fullfill their specific trope. Stories are made as a background for what the game is really about: dating. Hatoful Boyfriend isn't like that. Hatoful Boyfriend takes all the tropes from your average Otome Games and flips them of their heads making a refreshing change in the genre. Have you ever wondered why you'll fail in so many games if you don't date any of the guys? Hatoful Boyfriend explains it. All the characters have strong personalities and they don't feel so stale and one-dimensional. Sure, there's the shy quiet one and the obnoxious popular type, but there's so much more to it than that and every replay doesn't feel like a waste of time as you're actually learning more and more about the world they live in.Every tiny detail with each of the endings makes you more and more curious as to what the ♥♥♥♥ is going on. The humour and absolute strangeness will bring you in, but the complex storytelling and interesting characters will keep you playing until the end. These pigeons aren't here just to be weird and make sales. They exist for a reason. They exist for a fully devoloped and well thought out reason and it's absolutely worth buying and playing to find out what that reason is first hand. I promise you'll be pleasantly surprised."
