,Recommended,310080,33362181,Posted: 7 July,all,bird on skateboard,"My wife passed away in 2013. It was a very difficult time for me and my wife's son. I was working long hours and trying to raise my baby daughter. My wife's son was just entering high school. Life was hitting both of us hard. He was depressed most of the time. His grades started falling that year. I couldn't spend all too much time with him because of work. I had to stay at the office late most nights to pay for the nanny for my baby daughter. I bought him a playstation earlier that year. I was always into games, and I got the feeling he liked games too. He had a ds which he liked to play Kirby on. While I could never find the time to game, my coworker Jeff would always tell me about the current gems. He got me to buy my wife's son Little Big Planet. Jeff would always talk to me about Japanese visual novels. He told me about the brilliant dialogue and character choices. I thought about buying one for my wife's son, but he was still only 14 and he was still performing poorly in school. One day, Jeff started chatting me up about a new visual novel that had come out- Hatoful Boyfriend. Right before Christmas (my wife's son is 15 now) I decided to buy it for my wife's son. He was thrilled and surprised. He had never had an VN. He told me he had played one once at a friends house but that was it. He rarely went to friends' houses anymore. That Christmas I got a raise at work. I spent the holiday relaxed with my kids. I was initially concerned when I saw all the racism, crude language, violence, and sexual content in the game. The game even opened to a scene of the player being late to school, which I certainly didn't want my wife's son to emulate! On top of that, the game was very difficult. My wife's son often made me trade off with him, but I did not do much better. The Iwamine romance route was a deathwish! I had a little get-together on New Years and had some friends over and I used it as an opportunity for Jeff to help my wife's son and I in the game. I had to get back to work, but mywife's  son's break from school hadn't ended yet. He stayed home and gamed while I sat at work and day-dreamed about St. Pigeonation's Institute. I managed to find most of the songs from the game and I would listen to them on my computer at work. 静寂の海, 散り逝くなら、いっそ残酷に, and 過ぎ去りし日々 were and still are my favorites. At night when I would get home, we would eat dinner as a family and he would give me updates. We would smile and laugh and talk about some more adult themes. I found this game to be a great way to bond with my wife's son. The week ended and my wife's son went back to school. I told the nanny to try to help him manage his time with the game and homework. She made me pay her extra for that. At the end of the year, my wife's son brought home his report card. All A's second semester! I was so proud of him. I would later buy him Hatoful Boyfriend: Holiday Star, and I would find more time to spend with my wife's son and daughter. My wife's son continued to do good in school. In Senior Year, he got a job. I would help him buy new games, but he made his own money. He would have friends over and they would all play the new Nekopara. I gave him my car in 2016. He said it was the happiest day of his life. My wife's son is in college now. He calls me regularly. I help to pay for his needs, but he still has his old high school job. Now I try to spend quality time with my daughter. She is very smart and pretty. I've never missed one of her soccer games. She is very popular so she is always saying the night at her friends house. I eat dinner by myself, but I smile as I sit at our dinner table and I remember feeding my daughter, sitting on my lap, while my wife's son talks to be about the Bad Boy's Love ending. After dinner, I sit at my computer and play Hatoful Boyfriend. It is the best game ever made. Maybe if PigeoNation makes another Hatoful Boyfriend game, I can have my wife's son over again."
