,Recommended,310080,28998257,Posted: 3 January,all,Ticia,"Oh my, how I've been excited to write a review for this game! I'll try my best to keep it short and sweet.'Hatoful Boyfriend' is, essentially, a dating sim made up of visual novels...but...wait for it...involving birds! Yes. Each one has a different personality, and a corresponding physical design that resembles...WAIT FOR IT...an anime guy! *Wipes away happy tears*.You have a chance to spend time with just about every bird in the game, in some way or rather. However, said interactions are never inappropriate; which is good for the appeal of numerous audiences, as a collective. Although, I can disclose that some routes of this game, and also the ending [which is approximately 8 chapters long], are both deep and severely terrifying, in just as many ways as there is characters! ...If not more. So, if I were you, I personally wouldn't play this game unless you're 15+.As someone who's devoted all hours of the day(s...oops), take it from me. What you need to play 'Hatoful Boyfriend' is about 10 hours of uninterrupted play-time, an unending lot of patience, and a good interest for troubling storylines. A serious bonus requirement for surviving this game would also be to have a strong, emotionless heart! (I know right? Geez...)Anyway, um...Good luck! And enjoy the gorgeous otome pigeons!"
