,Recommended,310080,13744598,"Posted: 31 December, 2014",all,SailorTralfamadore,"Hatoful Boyfriend is a fun spin on traditional otome visual novels. Of course, that much is obvious from the very premise of the game: a dating sim involving pigeons! What really made Hatoful for me was how weird and/or creepy a lot of the endings were, especially the ""true ending"" in the form of the ""Bad Boys' Love""/Hurtful Boyfriend path that you unlock after achieving certain normal endings. I never expected to get this freaked-out by a game about dating pigeons! And on the happier side, Okosan's and Anghel's routes are amusingly weird, each in their own way. Still, some of the standard routes - including Ryouta's, Kazuaki's and Sakuya's, ones you need to achieve the BBL ending - are typical otome game stuff and don't have much to offer beyond that. But they're worth suffering through to get to the quality routes and to learn more about Hatoful's distinctive post-apocalyptic world. Give it a whirl even if you're not a VN fan."
,Recommended,310080,17342707,"Posted: 1 August, 2015",all,Mesigno,"Hatoful Boyfriend is a wonderfully bizzare RPG/Dating sim game, Not one normally for the Dating RPG genre I picked this up during the summer sale and was very plesently surprised it's quite different from the usual plod, with 13 different endings and a 14th ""Final end"" ending, the main 13 range from the utterly obsurd to actually quite moving which I thought was a nice touch and really added range to what felt possible in game, it's quite wittily written at times though the amount of Egg and Bird Puns does begin to wear a bit around about the 7th or 8th playthrough...its a pretty solid build of a game with my only gripe being the 14th ending known as the ""BBL"" ending. your milage may vary on it. but you'll either see it as A wonderful Amplifier that greatly adds depth and further character to what on the surface is a fairly light hearted game. or a very over played bloated add on to  the game that only seems to add a small book of texts worth of story with little to no choice in the matter... I personally saw it as the latter but I know there are some people out there that like that kind of detail.Also everyone is Pigeons..."
