,Not Recommended,310080,13752592,"Posted: 31 December, 2014",all,Fishbus,"A cute game with an interesting premise that unfortunately doesn't subvert the genre enough to make it not feel like an actual dating-sim.Dating sims are one of those really untouchable games for me, I think they are dumb, weird and creepy. Yet, Hatoful Boyfriend seemed like it was going to really appeal to the masses through a bit of satire, parody and commentary. I guess it does do that in a way, if not much, which is probably why it's had a radiating but mild success in other demographics. But I expected more, like some more gameplay, or branching interactions to really throw the competitors of the genre in the mud since they rely only on horrible anime pseudo porn. If it were to be a great parody AND to also include some legit gameplay, animations or more story depth and length, to really show others how to really make an interesting 'dating' sim at the same time would have elevated it to a great GAME, not some cheap feeling visual novella with around 10 input screens.Hatoful Boyfriend on the surface seems to only jest at the dialog of the genre in a very absurd  'lol dating games amirite?!' sort of way. Sure, some of the writing is silly, a bit fun, sometimes humorous and sometimes dark. But that's all you get, it still feels like i'm just playing an odd dating simulator after a few playthroughs.  Call me crazy but if there was a hint of a descent into madness, I would have liked to have seen a glimpse of it within the first hour of playing so I would be enticed to keep on digging deeper.Maybe I was expecting something along the lines of The Stanley Parable or (more hoping) Frog Fractions from what I heard from other people. But alas it doesn't. If it does, however, devolve into an exciting madness, I did not get that impression during my time playing.As a side note: It would have been nice to remember your username each time you played through but this is just nitpicking.Anyway, maybe I'm wrong about the whole thing and everything I said actually exists and things get crazy and engaging or even quite long. But it never seems to, and it never did.It's a shame really, I hope someone does revisit this type of game again and really make it into something odd, slick and compelling."
