,Not Recommended,310080,13859795,"Posted: 5 January, 2015",all,Lt. Don Draper,"Just a note: I am barely into this game. These are first impressions of the style of the game rather than the total storyline; please note this before judging my judgement.It's a game I could see people enjoying, and the positive reviews will drown out this one negative review(as well as the negative votes that this review will receive, as does any review which goes against popular opinion).First Impressions; writing style; quick comparison to other VNsI went into this game expecting a typical visual novel experience I had seen in Katawa Shoujo, Everlasting Summer/Beskonechnoye Leto, and other more casual/lesser visual novels. I was excited to prove my friend, having declined my offer of gifting this game, wrong, because I thought this would be a game on par with others with a unique and funny background. Unfortunately, it really has no poetic language, no charm, and no depth to the writing style. It is simply indicative in all instances, stating what happens and who does something. The main character is a typical girl and writes typically. There's no philosophical dialogue, and barely even character insight.It gets the job done, but I don't like the job it is doing. The task of quickly showing 2 minute scenes, switching between random choices and introducing a too-large amount of birds so quickly innundates any reader which is attempting to read at a normal or fast pace.I really want to iterate this. Each scene lasts a matter of minutes.Five minutes would be a very long event in this game.The scenery is okay. No places seem to be visited enough to be memorable past the Cafe and the main character's home. I really like the human portraits for each bird.NegativesShallow writing styleExtremely short encountersCharacters are either over-done or completely forgottenChoosing birds makes characters hard to remember (although this may be overlooked if you are good in memory)Simply isn't worth the money when compared to the plethora of hours free visual novels can supplyWasn't this game free before it was on Steam?PositivesEasy readfor those learning English as a second languageUnique background, birds have never been done before in such a wayI really do like the human portraits for each birdEasy to get into, and I've heard the storyline picks up farther in"
,Not Recommended,310080,15970256,"Posted: 23 May, 2015",all,Sikaran,"I was expecting clever social commentary and off-the-wall humor, but all I got was flat narration, lifeless dialogue, and forced drama.The menu options are also very primitive. There's no option to re-read text that has already scrolled past. Even Final Fantasy Tactics had that, and that was NOT a visual novel.There were a good number of typos as well.Soundtrack is repetitive and mostly uses stock copyright-free tunes.What a waste of money.Better options for PC gamers who are into visual novels would be Long Live The Queen (also available on Steam) and Katawa Shoujo (freely downloadable, but with WAY better production quality).Heck, even Come See Me Tonight, which was an eroge, had better writing than this."
