,Not Recommended,310080,16591081,"Posted: 21 June, 2015",all,Soundwave MD,"This game resonated with me about as much as RoboGeisha and Vampire Girl vs. Frankenstein Girl. To be blunt, it's a bit too weird to have a human character romance birds. That was the first issue.The real problem, though, in my opinion, is that this game is not interesting enough to play through the countless endings. Not only do you have to click through reams of text that you have already read several times, but you get to listen to the same handful of music loops, enjoy only the occasional choice, and see the same image for every character, regardless of where they are or what they are doing.I would be able to look past all of this if I found the jokes, plot, or characters worth the extra clicks. Heck, I used to enjoy playing flash RPGs several times in a row to both try new choices and enjoy the experience. I was hoping for a game that was chock-full of hilarious bird puns with maybe some nonsensical mischief and breaking of the fourth wall. In short, I expected this game to keep me in stitches.However (and I know this is strange to say about a bird dating simulator), the writing in this game is just not very memorable. Most of the jokes fall flat, the characters are unrelatable, and the overall story is lackluster. Perhaps if I got this game when I was younger I would have been able to enjoy it; as it is, this experience has reminded me that just because so many others have enjoyed a game does not mean I would.If you are into manga or want another joke game to give to/play with your friends, then buy Hatoful Boyfriend on sale. Otherwise, save the money."
