,Not Recommended,310080,18477115,"Posted: 14 October, 2015",all,DAvid,PLZZZ NO
,Recommended,310080,13857189,"Posted: 5 January, 2015",all,Phoenix,"I'll admit, I bought Hatoful Boyfriend because it's a game with birds, and Phoenix likes pretty much anything bird-related.  I kept reading snippets about how it's a really great game, and I caught it on sale and decided to get it on a lark (ha ha).  On the outside, you play the only human female at the world's most prestigious school for gifted birds.  Why you're a human female trying to find romance with birds is explained in the game if you play through all the various endings.  There are several possible story arcs in the game, and depending on which path you take you'll end up either falling in love with a specific bird, or have a completely unexpected turn of events.  Some endings are completely off the wall, others might be bittersweet.  That's just the surface though.  After completing enough of the correct story arcs, you'll unlock a much different story arc that provides backstory to all the characters and goes in a completely unexpected direction.  The story telling at that point is absolutely superb.As for how the game is played, it's basically in the format of a click-through novel with various choices.  The visuals are static backgrounds with static character graphics, and due to the nature of the game needing to be replayed, a lot of the narrative can become redundant.  There is a ""fast forward"" button that allows you to skip ahead between decision points.  There's a ""stat"" system that keeps track of your wisdom, vitality, and charisma based on what classes you choose and how you interact in certain situations.  These may look meaningless at first, but depending on which story path you choose they DO matter.The pros:It has birds.  You like birds right?There's a lot of obvious parody and downright silliness.It's simple to play.  No fancy controls, no real learning curve.The music is fantastic.The characters are unique and interesting.This is NOT a ""dating"" sim.  Romance plays an element, but there's a much deeper story line.It's not very expensive.There's no sexual content.  It's clean.The extended storyline is extremely well thought through and intricate.The cons:Playing through each storyline can get a little tedious.Some endings require you to have certain stats either high or low, and it's not obvious as to which.The lack of animation and static nature of the graphics will be a turn-off to some.There are some spelling and grammar errors that should have been caught.The simplistic nature of the interface and the fact that it's more of a ""choose your own adventure""-style novel and completely lacks any real skill element will be unattractive to people with short attention spans.There are some much darker elements that, if you're expecting just a light-hearted silly game, might catch you off-guard.Obiously this is not a game for everyone, but Phoenix likes it, so take a look and decide for yourself.One last note:  A lot of males will wonder, ""Ok, I'm a dude, why should I play this when it looks so girly?""  If you're of a mature intellect and you're comfortable with your gender identity, that should not scare you away.  This is not a ""girly"" game.  That's part of the parody aspect.  In addition, your character - not you - is the one the events happen to.  This character has her own thoughts and actions in the narrative.  You're just guiding her decisions.  Keep that in mind if you're on the fence."
