,Not Recommended,310080,12841228,"Posted: 8 November, 2014",all,theromulans,"I picked this game up on sale out of curiosity more than anything. I simply did not understand what was going on here and I needed to know more.There are a few different things going on here, and I'm not entirely compelled by any of them. There's the joke on date simulators - this is entertaining for a brief period of time. There's some wacky and unexpectedly great writing - this is interesting for a few hours. Then the story really gets going... and going... and going. While it was interesting to explore the full potential of the cast of characters and the setting I left the game feeling a bit like the joke was on me - my time had been wasted.I suppose part of my frustration comes to the Save Game feature intermittently working, causing my final run of the story get tiresome as I was unable to really leave it for another day. Perhaps I lost track of the different Japanese names that, at times, chop and change? Perhaps it's the lack of any actual branching choices in the last segment of the game that left it feeling shallow (from a 'game' point of view)?Hatoful Boyfriend is an interesting exercise but definitely not a game I'd recommend. Perhaps it's a game for a certain type of person - and not me."
