,Recommended,310080,12070516,"Posted: 12 September, 2014",all,rosemask22,"A great game for those who love the dating sim genre and a good game for those who don't.Hatoful Boyfriend is a parody dating sim where instead of romancing other people, you romance birds. The routes for each of the birds are fairly short compared to other dating sims out there but they are all funny and enjoyable (and some downright bizarre). However, if you're looking for a lot of romance, then I wouldn't say this game is for you. While there is romance in some routes, it is mainly left to the readers imagination after the route is finished. I would say though, that if you are a fan of dating sims and otome games, you will probably get more out of the game as it parodies stereotype characters found in a lot of typical dating sims.Even if you aren't a huge fan of dating sims, I would recommend the game alone for the alternative story which contrasts greatly to the main game (and is a lot longer than the average route). The alternative story answers all the mysteries hinted at in the main game and gives a explanation to why you are the only human in a school for birds. Let me just say, if you're a fan of mysteries and thrillers you will probably like this part.I actually bought the deluxe edition, which features: the soundtrack (36 tracks), the original game (in english), a ten page manga with 4koma strips and some illustrations (in both Japanese and English), two Okosan wallpapers and a 35 page yearbook, featuring pictures of the backgrounds and characters. While the extra stuff is great, I don't think I would pay full price for the deluxe pack. However, if you are a big fan of the series and the original game it might be worth it."
