,Recommended,310080,16424724,"Posted: 15 June, 2015",all,Ploonter,"I would highly reccomend Hatoful Boyfriend. If you don't like dating sims, you can appreciate the story behind the game. If you don't like the serious underlying tones, you can just focus on the dating aspect. If you don't like pigeons/doves, you can hook up with a quail.I'd give it an 9/10. The game is aThe art and music have their own flaws. Some of the art isn't super great (the backgrounds can be a little blotchy) and the music is just classic cheesy dating sim stuff, but it's all pretty decent anyway. You can play without the music and not miss anything, as there are no voice actors for the birds.Hatoful Boyfriend offers a unique amount of replayability. You can die, you can get two endings with some of the birds, and as you progress through the game through each bird's uniquely charming story, you essentially unlock an entirely different game. But keep in mind that after your second or third ending, it gets a bit tedious going through the dialogue. The fast forward button in the top right is your friend for that, but even that will get tedious if you're going for 14 endings. Be patient.This game is a slice of life wrapped up in an outlandish plot and humanistic birds that you can fall in love with. It's fun and it's charming and it's worth spending time and money on."
