,Recommended,310080,15703000,"Posted: 5 May, 2015",all,Lanky Kong,"Despite being a game about trying to get that bird butt, Hatoful Boyfriend is touching, heartwarming, heartbreaking, and fun. The obvious quirk to this game doesn't cause the game to get lost in that - the story is still cohesive, the characters are rich, and the world is filled with backstory to be discovered, and content to be explored outside of the game through ""real"" blogs by characters from that world.This game isn't for anyone who can't stand dating sims. On the surface it looks like it's a quirky little game about dating birds, and it is, but if you're not into reading lines and lines of dialogue, having long stretches of time where your only interaction is one line of dialogue, or what class to go to, or replaying over and over, this should be avoided. However, if you're a dating sim fan, or even someone who wants to get into them, this is worth picking up. It doesn't take itself too seriously, and it's a very light experience that's as powerful as you want it to be.10/10 I want to date these birds."
