76561198131904111,Recommended,310080,15527492,"Posted: 24 April, 2015",all,kamikaze9699,"I was originally planning on writing this only giving the three most interesting endings to shoot for and giving it a rating of ever-so-slightly entertaining, but after 100%ing it, I must say you should get at least 1 ending for all dates so you can go through the bonus fulfill the wish story. Don't let the fact you're going through the standard intro yet again bore you into quitting- the story diverges greatly from what you've played, and actually gets very interesting (assuming you can suspend you disbelief at the level the novel asks you to). Yeah, there are a few misspellings and instances of poor grammar (just as with the rest of the game). But, if you're willing to do that, and don't mind linearity, then yes, this is worth the full price. If not...The normal game does a good job deconstructing the high school dating visual novel cliches, and the fact you're a human girl vying for the affections of a bird only adds a bit more humor to it. There's a fast-forward feature that skips to the next day or decision, so replays aren't that painful. My favorite endings in the standard game are the ones for the Fallen Angel, best Track Star, and best Doctor. If you're not willing to go through all the endings and don't want to go through the bonus story, then I'd wait for it to go on sale. If you're more of a completionist, I'll say it again- I was very impressed by the bonus story, and completely taken by surprise that the writers could craft some junkfood for the mind that good. The bonus epilogue isn't that good, so it's up to how much of a completionist you are if you shoot for that as well. But the bonus story is worth the money and the effort of unlocking it."
