,Recommended,310080,22921027,"Posted: 11 May, 2016",all,luna,"this game is like any other otome game- only it has birds and everyone has their own plot twists you'd think it'd be satirewell, somehowI went through Nageki's route first because I'm a book lover too but go D D aMn I did not expect that- I seriously couldn't do anything for minutes and my heart was numbbut anyways- this game is mediocre, it's passes standards, yes; it makes your heart churn at make you laugh at the same time, yes- I recommend this game to anyone who wants to experience playing otome games, but I wouldn't say this to be -the- best otome game there ever ispros:-Birds with personality! They also have their own unique backgrounds and you can adore them easily (with the exception of the doctor- I had the unfortunate luck to play Yuuya's before Shuu's and god frick I couldn't -stomach- Shuu's route at all, Yuuya was my second conquest after all :( )-The options are pretty blunt. The protagonist would always say which characters goes with what option, although it might be pretty hard for you first time to actually organize your options for one exact route-The routes are very short (in my opinion, I -am- accustomed to games like hakuouki, whose routes are v e r y long) so this game can easily become a past time if you find yourself doing nothing during a lazy day-The endings are realistic- or as realistic an otome game can get, there's a dash of cliche tucked in there but the ending's can at least satisfy the player (or if not- the calming end credits music always helps, man I love that ost)cons:-The routes are too short for my liking. (Weird, this is -both- a pro and a con? huh) Short routes don't usually immerse the player too much into the story, and I sometimes just find myself playing this game for the achievements alone-There's no compatibility/likeability/love gauge (or whatever you call that) for the characters you're aiming for. You're only going to realize that you've done the right thing if his dialogue is different from the other options, and sometimes not at all. Love gauges are v e r y important in otome games, especially if it's just at the start of the game, so you can know if you're going through the right path, so the player can easily be killed by the hawk's party if without a guide at their first try-It kind of gets repetitive over time until you finally get near the end, when both of you and your conquest are really bonded. I found myself skipping dialogue a lot, making this already short game even shorter-The stats system is very vague, like sure, you'll find yourself passing if you go to math class a lot and meet your conquests a lot more if you take classes associated with them, but suddenly you're faced with a turn based battle with your damage and hp depending on your stats and you wouldn't even realize how important that one class was to this route until you're hit with it with a loud smack, heck, even some endings require attending only one specific class for the whole year, and if you stray even one time from that class, in hopes of balancing your stats, you can say bye to your true endingthat's all I can say for now, but this is a fun game nonetheless, this game is worth the money, although I still recommend waiting for sales if you're tight on the money (this game was just on sale a week ago, and I was so angry because right after I bought it for its full price does steam decide to put it on a 75% sale, I was raging over twt so much)"
