76561197992856964,Recommended,310080,16885968,"Posted: 4 July, 2015",all,[FOR]mica,"This is a dating sim about birds, at bird university.  You play the only human student, who lives in a cave nearby.  There have been some disappearances lately, but half of the endings never touch on that.  The ones that do get very bloody, very quickly.There's a bit of new game plus, in that the options leading to the more...esoteric... endings are not available until after you've played through the game a few times, and there's one ending that unlocks only after you've gotten all of the others.Highly recommended, if you need a bit of madness in your day.  Or if you like stories that weave together at the last possible moment, like the Zero Escape games."
,Recommended,310080,16887163,"Posted: 4 July, 2015",all,Frozen Fireball,"All that can be said about how bizarre the premise is has already been brought up in other reviews, so I'm just going to skip right to the real question; is this game worth buying?Pros:-The story is surprisingly deep.  Once you get over how strange it is, it's a fascinating world, and even though you only see part of it, it feels like there's a lot more going on out there.-The characters all have their own unique personalities; it's difficult to find yourself bored by them.  My least favorite route was still interesting enough for me to enjoy.-Lots of replay value.  Each route that you take reveals a little more about the world, which, as I mentioned above, is quite fascinating.  Be sure to play again after getting all the endings.  It's definitely worth it.-This story has both a great sense of humor, and a surprisingly good sense of drama.  Stick with it to the end, and I can almost guarantee that you will have shed at least a single tear over these characters.-This is the only game of its kind, so I can say in no uncertain terms that this is the best pigeon dating simulation on the market.Cons:-The save feature is totally broken.  You're going to want to play through an entire route in one sitting, because loading a game won't actually work about half the time.  The game itself doesn't take THAT long, so it isn't a total deal-breaker, but it's probably one of the most frustrating things about the game.-Despite the replay value, you're going to find yourself sitting through the same dialogue over and over again.  Each route has its own unique dialogue, too, but there are scenes that happen in every single playthrough regardless of your choices.  Mitigated somewhat by the fast forward button, but then you might end up missing some new dialogue by mistake.  That, and the fast forward still isn't that fast when you're sitting through the intro for the umpteenth time.-If I remember correctly, three characters have both a normal and a true ending, and - unless by some incredibly stroke of luck, the save feature is actually working correctly for you - you're going to have to play through the exact same route making only slight alterations to your stat choices to get both.  I ended up getting the true ending for two out of the three the first time I played, so I ended up spending two entire, tedious games fast-forwarding through dialogue I'd already seen.  It would be a little forgivable if the endings were actually different, but the ""true"" ending is just the same exact ending with a single short, extra scene tacked on.  This is unnecessary padding; I wish they'd just count it as both endings if you got the true ending the first time.Conclusion: This game has a fantastic story told through bits and pieces in various playthroughs, and a great sense of humor.  Endings range from predictable to totally out of left field.  You'll probably have a favorite pigeon by the end of it all.  Mine is Shuu.  :D  Still, fun as it is, it isn't without its flaws.  There IS content you can only unlock by getting all of the endings, and as I said, that can be a tedious process.  This content is well, WELL worth the effort, though; I can promise you that much.  Just make sure to use all the save slots in your final playthrough, since it's rather long, and if you have to quit in the middle of it, you don't want to put all your eggs in one basket.  In my experience, a save is more likely to work if a bird portrait isn't on screen behind it at the time, but that could just be a fluke.  Good luck with that.  ^^'  Anyway, I have to recommend this game, but do keep those issues in mind.  If you can, get the normal endings before the perfect ones so you'll at least have some new content to look forward to at the end of the second run."
