76561198106597850,Recommended,310080,17152911,"Posted: 21 July, 2015",all,Muddy Armadillo,"Hatoful Boyfriend is easily one of the best games I've ever played, and the ""gimmick"" that is a ""dating sim with birds"" quickly reveals some of the most interesting (and surprisingly dark) backstory I've seen in a game. The positives of this game cannot be over-stated, and though it may start a little rough, it will quickly fly its way into your heart.Positives+Engaging and distinctive characters with branching story paths that encourage multiple playthroughs.+Tremendous writing that gradually sets up the strange, comedic, and dark world that you (the protagonist) is residing in.+Multiple endings and characters, including some secret ones!+Puns... So many puns...+Great music selection that excellently promotes the tense, calm, and (most importantly) romantic moments that you'll be experiencing with the birds.Negatives-During the ""courting"" section of the game, you'll be asked to pick from a variety of seeds to give to your feathered lover. While you'll eventually learn the different preferences, the game offers no clear explanation of which bird likes what, and it often will turn into a guessing game.-A similar complaint appears with the ""skill raising"" portions that occur during regular parts of the game. It's not really made clear (except in obvious cases) what skills will help most with a specific bird. As with the first negative, this turns the game into ""trial and error"", something I don't enjoy in any game.Taken as a complete package, Hatoful Boyfriend is an amazing game, even if you're not a fan of the typical ""Japanese dating sim"" genre. A memorable and diverse cast of characters, deep storylines filled with comedy, tragedy, and romance, and the environment that the game creates are good enough reasons to overlook the ""trial and error"" portions that initially slow it down. All in all, Hatoful Boyfriend is a tremendous game, and deserves to be given a chance, if only for its sheer creativity and the opportunity to drown the world in pudding."
