,Recommended,310080,17134320,"Posted: 19 July, 2015",all,Cactus Deity,"I never thought I'd be reviewing a bird dating simulator, let alone this positively, but here I am, so if that doesn't say enough already...I bought this game a few months back on a whim while it was 40% off. I started off not expecting too much, since visual novels aren't my thing and I figured it was pretty much a just dating sim parody filled with bird puns. It is a dating sim parody filled with bird puns, but it's also much more.See, visual novels aren't my type because I'd rather have storyline mixed with more effort on my part than just clicking, but I think this was done really well. Your choices throughout the game are quite obvious as to whatever bird the decision would earn you favor with. However, the storyline is fleshed out. Like, really fleshed out. I don't have experience with dating sims but I can tell this one has a lot more going on than usual, despite the obvious fact that they're birds.So the storyline seems pretty out there at first. You're an unquestioned human girl at a school for birds, in a city of birds. You can date the birds. Or, if you don't court a bird properly, you'llbe murdered in your home in the middle of the night. Anyway, as you date these birds, you get a story out of each of them. Your sickly best friend, the stand-offish french transfer student, the eccentric track captain, the narcoleptic teacher, the quiet freshman, the flirty upperclassman, the bone-chilling school doctor, and the bizarre fallen angel are all choices where you can find love. However, once you've gone through the game a few times, the start screen informs you that instead of playing the regular game, you can choose to fulfill a promise from long ago... which pulls you into the ending that ties all their stories togetherinto a tale of how the world is post apocalyptic after scientists tried to wipe out birds that had deadly bird flu and had it backfire, mutating the birds which then gained the intelligence to retaliate against humankind. If you want to know more than that, seriously, just buy it. It should be noted that I started the endgame expecting it to be 15 minutes long then found myself finishing it at 3 AM that night.The mechanics are simple, gameplay surprisingly isn't too slow for my tastes, and even though parts can feel slow after you've played dating a few birds, you can fast forward through parts.If you have the time and the patience for something slow going but interesting, please do yourself a favor and buy this game. Do it for the birds."
