,Recommended,310080,12307111,"Posted: 30 September, 2014",all,すみか,"Hatoful Boyfriend is an interesting experience.  I think a lot of people go in not really knowing just what to expect.  I mean, on the surface all you see is a Visual Novel and Dating Sim where almost all the characters are birds.  The normal reaction to that is to say ""...uh, wait.  What?""  But after you spend some time in the game, getting to know the characters and the world the whole bird thing just kind of shifts off to the side.  Your brain starts to think of it as normal.  I'm not really sure why, if it is because of the clever writing, the wonderfully crafted characters, or if I'm  just weird.  The most interesting thing about Hatoful Boyfriend however is that it manages to scratch every single itch a player would have when it comes to a Visual Novel type experience.  Did you want something light hearted and funny?  There is a path for that.  Did you want something super creepy?  Hey, we got a path for that too.  How about something epic and grand complete with a throw back reference to old school JRPGs and some rocking tunes?  You know what?  It actually has that too.  That just scratches the surface.But most importantly, after you go through and finish each of the characters endings something magical happens: You get to fulfill a promise from long ago.  Not only do you have a shift in the game once more but you actually get the real meat of the experience and all the details that make up the world the game is set in.  And it is glorious.  Absolutely glorious.Score: 8 / 10"
