,Recommended,310080,12241760,"Posted: 25 September, 2014",all,lowcast,birds are ok bffs meow
,Recommended,310080,12280763,"Posted: 28 September, 2014",all,John,"Hatoful Boyfriend is a pretty simple game, in terms of gameplay; you read through story bits, every now and then you make a choice. Depending on your choices, you ultimately get to an ending; getting certain endings unlocks other options for other stories. Simple. The real attraction, therefore, is in the story. The premise is frankly insane; you are the only human attending a school for intelligent birds. And yet...And yet the premise is developed in a consistent and plausible way. All the characters are fully realized, and it's easy to get emotionally invested. If you go through every storyline, little bits that seemed filler will suddenly take on a larger context, and you'll realize that a *lot* of work went into the story. But even in the most emotional storylines, there are bits that will come out of nowhere and make you go ""WTF!"". That's the thing that really impresses me, that the game is consistently surprising. At turns cheery, tragic, silly, absurd, gruesome, parodic, heartwrenching and insane, it's an experience I can't help but recommend."
