,Recommended,310080,11986152,"Posted: 5 September, 2014",all,Osprey Man,"First of all, I played the game in its original release, so don't let my play time fool you. I've put far more hours into this game than most.It sounds like a bizarre combination at first- a dating game with pigeons. No doubt, Hatoful Boyfriend creates a world where a healthy dose of belief-suspension is in order. But beneath that silly exterior is a tale that's sweet, funny, dramatic, endearing, and very cute.If you're a bird lover like I am, you'll find the world and its characters particularly charming, but you don't have to be one to connect with the cast. It's easy to forget the species of your schoolmates when you want to see how each of their stories unfold. Only the most shallow will let the fact they're pigeons get in the way of their emotional tales, which are spun to make the player laugh, love, and maybe even shed a tear here and there (anyone who watched me stream this game knows I sure did). It leans on the short side of duration, including all potential paths, but just like how it takes itself just seriously enough, the game gives you just enough to accomplish its goal without overstaying its welcome. It's succinct, hitting all the key points necessary to develop a world, tell a story, and make you interested in the characters, which is really all one can ask of it.Hatoful Boyfriend is a quirky little game that was made with love and is worth checking out, even if just to explore a dating sim from a different angle. And if you're a bird lover, then it's a must. As Oko-san would say, it's ""coo!"""
