,Recommended,310080,15065896,"Posted: 26 March, 2015",all,DoodleDragonZ,"Hatoful Boyfriend is a pretty quick play - all the paths (excluding the true ending) are short. You could potentially unlock all the paths and complete the entire game in a few hours.However, in that short time, the game packs an intricately dark plot, as each successive romance you complete reveals a surprising depth to each and every bird you meet. The true ending is the longest, and the darkest part of the game, and is well worth the time.Overall, an excellent storyline coupled with the absurdity of bird romance, but you'll burn through it in only a few hours. 9/10"
,Recommended,310080,15071312,"Posted: 26 March, 2015",all,Pijon,"Hatoful Boyfriend starts out as a straight-out parody of many visual novel tropes, letting the reader get to know and enjoy the personalities of each bird. The reader gets various clues throughout the main game that there's a lot more happening behind the scenes. By the end, the story turns into a psychological horror, turning each character on his head- making the reader question everything they have learned about the birds so far. Yes, this game is quite awesome- both in the original and the HD remake.Is it worth $10? I would say ""Yes, of course it is! BBL is worth $10 alone."" However, I have noticed a few things about this new polished version that make me miss the older, typo-ridden $5 version. These are certainly nitpicks. For one, I don't like the new desktop icon (pink heart with 2 feathers sticking out) It is the most Otome looking thing on my boyish desktop and it sticks out like a sore thumb. I much prefer the green nicobar logo. Secondly, while I am thankful this game has a fullscreen mode (which makes recording footage a breeze) I believe the original has a tiny window for a reason- mainly, the bird portraits are of varying quality. In fullscreen, I get to see all the choppy pixels I wasn't aware of before. Back to the tiny window I suppose. Azami's route, newly added in this version, was lackluster. This has been built up by fans for a while now and of course, its ""safe"" nature has nothing to do with the team that polished this game up. However, when I played it, I was a bit confused as to why Azami had a one-sided mad rant to herself when cleary, Hiyoko was supposed to say at least half of the lines. Maybe that issue has been sorted by now? My biggest issue is the Save feature in BBL! I am serious about this, it ruins the mood. While there is no real way to fail BBL, it was quite a shock to readers when they first play it. It was made even scarier when the box shows up saying that save states are disabled for this portion of the game. The survival instict kicks in for a lot of readers at that point.  Players would then be cautious about their surroundings and return to HQ repeatedly to make their alotted save. In this newer, sparklier version... the player can save whenever they well please- taking away that intense atmosphere. The ""battle"" at the end? No problem, they can just save and not have to worry about potential failure. Eh, I don't like that. But the backgrounds are absolutely gorgeous in this version, and I'm very glad that Nageki has lost his awkward clutching side-foot. Also, having the option to switch from English to Japanese with the click of a button is really nice. I am glad I bought this verion of the game.A few unrelated things I noticed while playing this game again... Some of our stud birdies appear to be female! Leone JB and Rabu both have pink ceres. Also... pigeon genders are hard to identify by appearance alone, but I will say that our OkoSan has a Very feminine skull. And Ryouta's portrait... well, look at those pupils! That is one miffed bird. Anghel and Shuu are puffed out like they're absolutely freezing, the poor birds. And... that fight music? While I know it is public domain- it is also the title menu music to a gory horror BL visual novel called Cage -open-. Imagine my shock as I see Anghel on one side of the screen, Shuu on the other side of the screen, and my auditory cue for shiver-inducing psychological torture♥♥♥♥♥♥triggers. ""My god Shuu, don't!  Oh wait, you have a harmless cloaka... Do what you must, then."""
