,Recommended,310080,12869491,"Posted: 9 November, 2014",all,Violit,"Most people have heard of the infamous 'bird dating simulator' because the premise is... well, seemingly ridiculous. You play as the only human in a school of birds and the object of the game is to form meaningful relationships with them. Yep, that's right, you're gonna pull yourself some sweet pigeon booty. Coo Coo. It seriously feels like a parody on the dating sim genre at best.The writing is mediocre at best with most of the birds being just as much as an oddball as the main character. The birds personalities do fall flat at time, but what really ties the game together is the 'true ending' which can only be obtained by playing through every bird's route. The true ending manages to effortlessly weave the links between all of the birds and Hiyko together leading to a story that has twists, surprises and tearjerking moments. The conclusion is satisying and enough to convince me that although this is a game with a ridiculous concept, it's meant to be taken seriously and not as the joke as it seems.Overall, Hatoful Boyfriend is a quirky game with a colourful cast of birds to romance and with enough twists and turns to remain fresh for every playful. The ability to fast forward through scenes is much appreciated and the game isn't a joke, no matter how hard it seems like one."
,Recommended,310080,12833065,"Posted: 7 November, 2014",all,Koko★,"You don't have to be an ornithologist to enjoy this game, this game is perfect for anyone who wants to try out a dating simulator with a twist. Also: compelling unlockable storyline. Worth!"
