,Recommended,310080,33068261,Posted: 30 June,all,AshelaainArtemis,"First off I wanna say this:Don't get turned off from the premesis of dating birbs, cuz trust me on this one, it may appear an innocent dating app, but it is anything but. Prepare to board the Rollarcoaster of Emotions -  Careful! It's gonna be a bumpy ride!I heard of this game a long time ago from a girlfriend of mine but never actually bought until the Summer sale this year (yeah I'm one of THOSE ppl). Like most others, at first glance the game is a visual novel & otome. Well... visual novel it is. Otome? Not exactly. DON'T BE FOOLED by the pretty pink and purple colors and the hearts on the promotional pictures for this game.I was completely blown out of the water with the twists of horror mixed in here - especially Shuu's! Even though his endings were a gruesome result, the way it's portrayed made it enjoyable to go through! Similar to a haunted house that gives you a tingly delight of scares. I read both romance and horror vn's so having them both in one game was the best thing ever for me. If you like sci-fi, romance, horror, & dark plots, then you'll love this game!That being said, I honestly would've preferred a happier ending then the one we got, but at the same time, I wouldn't want it to end any other way. Romance wise I'd say there are really only two I would call ""romance routes"". The others were kind of like ""oh yeah I like you but you'll have to wait"" sort of stories. If I counted correctly, there are four total horror endings, including The True Ending. The most graphic thing you see is blood seeping through a cardboard box - other than that, it doesn't SHOW most of the gruesome things that happen.So, if you can stomach the gruesome results on some routes, I would HIGHLY recommend playing this game."
76561198025203072,Recommended,310080,15957815,"Posted: 22 May, 2015",all,Parabones,"Hatoful boyfriend absolutely feels like a 'joke' game, as in, a game made on a drunken dare and meant to have been created on a whim, tossed on steam, and then forgotten about by the devs. It still is a joke game, really, and i'm not denying that this game relies on absurdist and situational humor. But, the difference between a purely joke game and this game, is that hatoful boyfriend has actual substance and worth behind it.I had known about this game for a while, and picked it up believing it would just be funny and silly and filled with bird puns, until I found myself legitimately crying at one of the endings. Then I laughed out loud because I was crying over a game about giant, sentient pigeons. Hatoful never forgets how really ridiculous it is at heart, but it is not afraid to still give you a memorable story and lovable, dynamic characters, even if they are just photos of a bird. Soon enough you start rooting for and yearing for the happiness of your favorite pidge and you wonder what the hell happened"
