76561198141501622,Recommended,310080,14998641,"Posted: 21 March, 2015",all,Gryphon_Spyder,"When I bought this game, I thought it was going to be ridiculous.And it was. This game has momets that make you laugh out loud simply because they are so freaking ludicrous.What I did not expect was how much I would care about this game. The storyline is fantastic. the characters are amazing. every story arc is interesting, every bird has more to them than meets the eye, and I was amazed at how many intense emotions this game made me feel. I was expecting to laugh, sure, but I was not expcecting to feel upset, I was not expecting to feel excited for tomorrow beyond ""Oh I wonder what the next joke is""; I was not expecting to be so emonionally invested in this game.There are at least a couple of story arcs that made me want to cry, and THAT is something that I was not expecting AT ALL.This game is fantastic. It knows that it is absurd, and takes full advantage of that fact.but it also manages to get you to take it seriously, too, and that was one of the things about this game that impressed me the most; a game about a human dating pigeons that manages to evoke strong emotions, has a deeper underlying story, and most importanly, makes you feel like most of the characters are more than just silly pictures of pigeons on a computer screen: this game gives everyone a personality and a story, and it makes characters appear far simpler than they truly are multiple times. Every new playthrough gives you a new understanding of the characters and makes them that much more like real people."
