,Recommended,310080,13863088,"Posted: 6 January, 2015",all,[Slasher],"This game will twist the very fabric of your reality. Every bird you encounter after this game will seem to hold an intriguing mystery, a sinister backstory, and a beguiling air. If you like adventure, romance, conspiracy, murder, and birds, this is the game for you. The first half of the game is as promised - a fun, wacky dating sim involving birds and school life. Some strange things may pique your interest, but it all seems part of the fun. Then you get to the second half of the story (only unlocked once you have played through dating all the birds, except San) and everything, EVERYTHING gets turned on its head.I have no words to describe the mind-bending experience that is the second half. Not so much a game as an extremely gripping visual novel that's a wild ride from start to finish. Everything is explained, all loose ends tied, a game that must be played twice - nay, three times to fully comprehend the utter brilliance of its story. At times touching and melancholic, at times hilarious and baffling, but always with a keen sense of incredulity (""I can't believe these are BIRDS""), this is a game that will haunt you, I promise. If you ever get an avian-related game, forget Flappy Bird, GET THIS GAME."
