,Recommended,310080,15045592,"Posted: 25 March, 2015",all,V2Blast,"This game is even better than the premise makes it out to be.I have spent the past few days playing through each of the many routes of Hatoful Boyfriend from start to finish. I had heard there was quite a bit of hidden depth to this game... But I was not expecting as much of it as there was. Of the various routes in the game, some were more emotional than others, and some were downright silly. By chance, I started off with what seemed to be among the most emotional of them all, so several of the other routes were a little disappointing by comparison. There were references to Pokemon and Gurren Lagann and other popular culture littered throughout the visual novel, which was entertaining for a time, but they're not so overused as to come off as trying too hard to be funny. Honestly, for the most part, you should just treat 90% of those routes as a basic introduction to the characters.Then I started the final route. It starts out almost the same... And then takes a huge left turn. It is basically a totally different game, and pretty much my primary reason for recommending the game. It answers all the questions brought up and never answered in the other routes (and some you might not even have thought of). It's *very* emotional at times, and just generally intense. So if you play a few routes and aren't too impressed, hang in there. It is worth it.It's almost certainly worth $10, and you should definitely get it if it's on sale. The soundtrack is comprised of a bunch of short, looping songs, but the writing/translation is surprisingly good (barring a few occasional mistakes like missing words), and the story turned out to be really compelling. You'll laugh, you might cry, you'll definitely say ""holy♥♥♥♥♥♥quot; a few times.Buy it. You will not regret it."
