,Recommended,310080,13971169,"Posted: 13 January, 2015",all,Tegernseher,"This game is... different. It is basically a ""choose your own adventure"" novel. There is no gameplay apart from clicking and reading and making choices. No quicktime-events like in The Walking Dead or The Wolf Among Us. If that does not suit you, do not buy this game. If, however, you are a fan of stories and twisted narrative, you should definitely get it. The protagonist is a human, attending a bird-school and the main goal is to flirt and date the various characters that can be met. This sounds crazy and boring, but it is not. This game is just f*cked up. The graphics are not worth mentioning, the soundtrack however suits the game pretty nicely. The writing can get you hooked, if you are ready to ignore the typos that occur from time to time. The first playthrough should take about 2 hours, but there is replay-value, as there are several different endings. It is not for everybody, but if you want something new and crazy, this is probably a game for you."
