,Recommended,310080,16612369,"Posted: 21 June, 2015",all,Snow,"Hatoful Boyfriend is, at its core, beautifully ridiculous. I mean, what more would you expect from a game about dating birds? But at the same time, it's so much more. It's charmingly light-hearted and incredibly deep. It'll make you laugh your♥♥♥♥♥off and cry your eyes out, possibly in one sitting. It has one of the best stories of any dating sim I've ever played, perhaps even of any video game at all.At one point, I was sobbing so loudly my sister came in my room to make sure I was ok (it's alright sis, I'm crying over pigeons). 11/10 would cry over again.UPDATE: My sister played it and cried no less than 4 times."
,Recommended,310080,20605138,"Posted: 18 January, 2016",all,Fallen_Castiel,"I got this game because my best friend was playing it, and even though it seemed silly, I thought it might be fun. I was too curious about it, so I bought it. I am not sorry at all! I thought it would just be completely ridiculous, which let's be honest, it should be, because they are all pigeons, but it's not. You quickly become wrapped up in stories that actually evoke feelings, stories as well written as any dating sim I have played. This ends up being better than some of the things it is supposed to be a parody of.I recommend this highly if you enjoy dating sims, but want a bit of humor too. It is really enjoyable, and has mulitiple endings, so each play through is really great. I am only at four endings now. It actually is challenging to get some of them as well, not as easy as you would think!Have fun!"
76561198152031977,Recommended,310080,20643405,"Posted: 20 January, 2016",all,Platy,"This game isn't even big on the dating aspect. Compared to other visual novels/dating sims, Hatoful Boyfriend is a lot more straight to the point and fun to read, no endless rambling from the mc here. She is actually quite transparent but not in a dull way that you expect from most otome games.Most routes can be completed within an hour, but rather than actually seducing the pigeons it's more like you get to know them better. All in preparation for the BBL route which you get once you've unlocked every boy's ending.Hatoful Boyfriend seems just like a random silly game you'd play so you can comment 'Pigeons lulz!!"" and make crappy bird puns on the internet, but the story turns out to be dark enough to keep you coming back for more. The way every character is woven into the big scheme of things here was really well done. Also there are no ero-scenes, which doesn't impact the game in the slightest. Nevertheless the endings (There are 16 in total) are very rewarding.I thought it would just be a silly game, but I found myself really enjoying the narrative and trying to piece things together. Also I got a few laughs out of this and have a crush on a few characters. The soundtrack isn't bad either and the dialogue is quite funny.Overall, a lot better than anyone would expect."
