,Recommended,310080,20413477,"Posted: 8 January, 2016",all,Kol-Ut-Shan,"When I bought Hatoful Boyfriend in the Winter Sale, I had no idea what the game was about, other than ""pigeon dating sim"". I expected to get a few laughs and maybe 2-3 hours of gameplay before I got bored and moved on to something else. But when my character mentionedbeing a hunter-gathererwithin the first few minutes, I knew that there had to be more to it than that.As I continued through the game, I found that it was not only much more amusing than I'd expected, but that the characters were genuinely engaging--particularly Okosan (tiny brain, big heart), Sakuya (imagine if Draco Malfoy were a) likeable and b) a fantail pigeon), and Yuuya (a mysterious ladies' man). The first time I played, I got the bad ending because I liked all of the birds so much that I couldn't decide which one to focus on!After that, I felt like I had to stick around and get all of the characters' endings. It helped that after the first run-through, there was a fast forward button that allowed me to skip sequences I'd seen before. Following most endings, I'd find a new entry in the ""Archive"" section of the game that hinted at a convoluted backstory. And once I'd finished with all that, I found a new option available in the beginning of the game that unlocked therealstory, which was unexpectedly dark and twisted.This is honestly one of the most entertaining games I've ever played and I would recommend it to just about anyone. I'm picking up the sequel as soon as I post this review."
