,Recommended,310080,13947558,"Posted: 11 January, 2015",all,Real,"I have 18 hours of this game on record. You would look at me and think ""Wow, what a weirdo, plays 18 hours of bird dating."". But this game is far more than bird dating!At first i said ""Hihihi, stupid visual novel with pigeons, hihihi"". There are 9 birds who are dateable, each has one unique story and each story concludes in an ending. 3 endings can be extended to 'true endings' by visiting certain classes and gaining points (you are a student). These endings are somewhat surprising and often either expectedly funny or exceptionally emotional.After you romanced each bird once, you gain the ability to play the 'Bad Boys Love'-Story. This story is heartwrecking! It concludes every other storyline by answering any leftover questions. It plays maybe 5 times as long as a normal storyline and it can be quite difficult to follow at times, but in the end (and inbetween), at least i found myself near tears ;_;At the very latest then (like midway through the BBL-story) you realize, this game has not only bird-dating. It hasreligious themes, political themes, a James Bond equivalent, nazis, acurate scientific explanations, though describing inexplicable actions (birds dont have hands), zombie-robots, RPG-fights, and MORE!And bird-dating.10/10 would date again"
