76561198331946972,Recommended,310080,33728565,Posted: 22 July,all,╬Shiro_Han╬,"""Mom, Dad, the good news is I finally have a boyfriend. The bad news ......................................................................................................................................................................................................................................................................................................................He's a pigeon.""=====================================================================================Not for the serious Otome Game Players and people who feel uneasy to date birds.But if you're curious about a life of the only human girl who attends a school for birds, congrats! Go buy this game!You will experience  a few chuckles here and there, esp. with some scenes, plus some moans and groans with the bird puns. (As told by the reviewers before me...)This game may fall under a Romantic-Comedy genre but you thought wrong, looks can be deceiving.Anyway, like most games, this game has a few bugs.(1) The part where you choose the extracurricular activites (i.e.) Student Council, Track Team, etc. When you save on that said part and decided to load on that same save slot, (if you made a mistake later in the game or fed up having clicking the new game option, after you have finished any of the bird's route). The choice for the Infirmary Staff is not available.So you have to go back to the beginning, wait, and save on the previous dialogue box, before the extra-curricular options are given to you by the teacher.(2) Sometimes the skip button doesn't work. (As like most Otome Games, the urge to click the skip button is strong, especially when you finished a route and have to start all over again)(3) Some choice buttons are needed to be click a few times, in order for you to proceed.Those are the bugs that I have encountered, so far.The storyline is kind of unique especially at the end, (I REALLY did not expected that). The heroine's personality is somewhat bland,though she has more common sense than the heroine from the previous Otome Game I played with. The characters' relationship with each other are well-written,esp. with the brothers.While, the character development is so-so,except for Nageki, Sakuya, his older brother, Yuuya and the teacher, Kuzuaki.Grammar can be easily overlooked (unless you are as severe as an English Teacher). There are no voices on this game, neither are the chirps. Some of the background music can be found quite catchy.Overall, Hatoful Boyfriend is one of the Otome Games that I found it memorable and enjoyable.====================================================================================If you want to buy the bundle,( the DLC, and it's sequel), but found yourself unsure, i.e. if the price is worth it. I suggest to wait for the sale season."
